---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Ambotti Thampuran | Temple Administrator | Nagayakshi Temple">
  
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="thampuran-hero">
    <div class="thampuran-hero-overlay"></div>
    <div class="thampuran-hero-content">
      <h1>Ambotti Thampuran</h1>
      <p>Hereditary Administrator & Guardian of the Sacred Tradition</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Introduction -->
  <section class="intro-section">
    <div class="thampuran-container">
      <div class="intro-content">
        <div class="intro-image">
          <img src="/images/Ambotti.jpg" alt="Ambotti Thampuran" style="filter: sepia(0.2);">
          <div class="image-caption">Ambotti Thampuran, Temple Administrator</div>
        </div>
        <div class="intro-text">
          <h2>Guardian of Ancient Tradition</h2>
          <p class="intro-lead">
            As the custodian of Sree Pulikkal Vishwanagayakshi Temple, Ambotti Thampuran carries
            forward a sacred lineage spanning generations, ensuring the preservation of ancient rituals and the
            protection of the seven sacred Sarpa Kavus.
          </p>
          <p>
            Born into the noble Pulikkal Shankarodath Kovilakam family, he has dedicated his life to maintaining 
            the sanctity of this ancient shrine and serving the countless devotees who seek blessings from the 
            Divine Nagas. His deep knowledge of traditional rituals, combined with his compassionate approach 
            to addressing devotees' spiritual needs, makes him a trusted guide for those seeking relief from 
            Sarpa Dosha and other life obstacles.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Lineage & Tradition -->
  <section class="lineage-section">
    <div class="thampuran-container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="section-label">Sacred Heritage</span>
        <h2>The Pulikkal Shankarodath Lineage</h2>
      </div>
      
      <div class="lineage-content">
        <p class="lineage-intro">
          The Shankarodath Kovilakam is an ancient noble family entrusted with the sacred responsibility
          of protecting and maintaining the Vishwanagayakshi Temple and its seven Sarpa Kavus. This sacred
          duty has been passed down through generations, with each Thampuran dedicating their life to preserving
          the ancient traditions established by Kashyapa Maharshi himself.
        </p>
        
        <div class="tradition-grid">
          <div class="tradition-card">
            <div class="tradition-icon">📜</div>
            <h3>Hereditary Guardianship</h3>
            <p>
              The role of Thampuran is not merely administrative—it is a spiritual responsibility passed through 
              bloodline. Each generation receives the sacred knowledge of rituals, mantras, and temple protocols 
              directly from their predecessors, ensuring unbroken continuity of tradition dating back centuries.
            </p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="tradition-card">
            <div class="tradition-icon">🕉️</div>
            <h3>Ritual Authority</h3>
            <p>
              Ambotti Thampuran oversees all major ceremonies and poojas performed at the temple, ensuring strict 
              adherence to Vedic protocols and traditional procedures. His presence and sanction are required for 
              the most important rituals, particularly the annual Kala Sarpa Bali and major homams.
            </p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="tradition-card">
            <div class="tradition-icon">🌳</div>
            <h3>Kavu Protection</h3>
            <p>
              The seven sacred Sarpa Kavus are under his direct guardianship. He ensures their preservation, 
              maintains their sanctity, and prevents any violation of the sacred groves. Each Kavu requires 
              specific care and spiritual maintenance, which he personally oversees.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Mission & Vision -->
  <section class="vision-section">
    <div class="thampuran-container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="section-label">Guiding Purpose</span>
        <h2>Mission for Temple & Devotees</h2>
      </div>
      
      <div class="vision-grid">
        <div class="vision-card primary">
          <h3>Preserve Ancient Traditions</h3>
          <p>
            "Our first duty is to maintain the purity of rituals exactly as they have been performed for 
            centuries. Every mantra, every offering, every procedure must remain authentic. This is not 
            just about preserving history—it's about maintaining the spiritual power that makes these 
            rituals effective for devotees."
          </p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="vision-card">
          <h3>Restore Sacred Kavus</h3>
          <p>
            The seven Sarpa Kavus require ongoing protection and restoration. Natural degradation, encroachment, 
            and modern development threaten these ancient groves. A major mission is to restore each Kavu to 
            its original sanctity, replant native trees, and create protective boundaries ensuring their 
            preservation for future generations.
          </p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="vision-card">
          <h3>Serve Devotees with Compassion</h3>
          <p>
            Beyond ritual administration, the role involves genuine care for devotees' spiritual wellbeing. 
            Many arrive with deep suffering—childlessness, financial ruin, health crises, marriage problems. 
            Each person deserves patient guidance, proper ritual recommendations, and follow-up care to ensure 
            they receive maximum benefit from their prayers.
          </p>
        </div>
        
        <div class="vision-card">
          <h3>Educate & Guide</h3>
          <p>
            Modern devotees often lack understanding of traditional rituals and their significance. Education 
            is crucial—explaining why certain poojas work, what spiritual principles are at play, and how 
            devotees should prepare and follow through. This bridges ancient wisdom with contemporary understanding.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Daily Responsibilities -->
  <section class="responsibilities-section">
    <div class="thampuran-container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2>Sacred Duties & Responsibilities</h2>
      </div>
      
      <div class="responsibilities-grid">
        <div class="duty-card">
          <h3>🌅 Daily Rituals</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Supervise morning temple opening and purification</li>
            <li>Oversee daily poojas and abhishekams</li>
            <li>Ensure proper maintenance of deity idols</li>
            <li>Personal prayers at each of the seven Kavus</li>
            <li>Evening deeparadhana supervision</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        
        <div class="duty-card">
          <h3>🙏 Devotee Guidance</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Personal consultation with devotees (by appointment)</li>
            <li>Recommending appropriate poojas based on problems</li>
            <li>Blessing devotees during major ceremonies</li>
            <li>Providing spiritual counseling</li>
            <li>Follow-up with devotees on remedy effectiveness</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        
        <div class="duty-card">
          <h3>🔥 Ritual Oversight</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Leading major homams and special ceremonies</li>
            <li>Training priests in traditional procedures</li>
            <li>Quality control for ritual materials</li>
            <li>Ensuring Vedic accuracy of mantras</li>
            <li>Sanctioning modifications only when necessary</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        
        <div class="duty-card">
          <h3>🌳 Temple Maintenance</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>Kavu preservation and restoration projects</li>
            <li>Temple infrastructure upkeep</li>
            <li>Financial management and accounting</li>
            <li>Coordination with government authorities</li>
            <li>Planning for temple expansion and improvements</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Kavu Preservation Initiative -->
  <section class="preservation-section">
    <div class="thampuran-container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <span class="section-label">Critical Mission</span>
        <h2>The Kavu Preservation Project</h2>
      </div>
      
      <div class="preservation-content">
        <p class="preservation-intro">
          "The greatest challenge we face is protecting the seven sacred Sarpa Kavus from the pressures of 
          modern development. These are not just tree groves—they are the very homes of the naga deities. 
          Without these Kavus, the temple loses its spiritual foundation."
        </p>
        
        <div class="preservation-grid">
          <div class="preservation-item">
            <h3>The Challenge</h3>
            <p>
              Over decades, natural degradation, lack of maintenance, and surrounding development have 
              threatened the integrity of several Kavus. Some have lost native trees, others face 
              encroachment, and a few require complete restoration to their original sacred status.
            </p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="preservation-item">
            <h3>The Vision</h3>
            <p>
              Restore all seven Kavus to pristine condition—replanting native species, creating protective 
              boundaries, conducting purification rituals, and establishing permanent maintenance systems. 
              Each Kavu should be a thriving sacred grove where devotees can feel the presence of the nagas.
            </p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="preservation-item">
            <h3>How You Can Help</h3>
            <p>
              The restoration requires significant resources—native saplings, boundary walls, ritual materials, 
              and ongoing maintenance. Devotees can contribute through Kavu adoption programs, Gau-daanam
              (sacred cow donation), or direct support for specific restoration projects.
            </p>
            <a href="/support" class="btn-preservation">Support Kavu Preservation →</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Trust Information -->
  <section class="trust-section">
    <div class="thampuran-container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2>Temple Trust & Administration</h2>
      </div>
      
      <div class="trust-content">
        <p class="trust-intro">
          The temple operates under traditional custodial guardianship, with Ambotti Thampuran as the
          principal authority. While maintaining ancient governance structures, the temple also ensures
          transparency and accountability in all operations.
        </p>
        
        <div class="trust-grid">
          <div class="trust-card">
            <h3>Traditional Structure</h3>
            <p>
              Unlike many modern temples under government or trust board control, Vishwanagayakshi Temple
              operates under its traditional custodial system. This ensures continuity of authentic
              practices and prevents bureaucratic interference with sacred rituals.
            </p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="trust-card">
            <h3>Financial Transparency</h3>
            <p>
              All donations and offerings are properly accounted for and used exclusively for temple purposes—
              ritual materials, priest dakshina, maintenance, and Kavu preservation. Regular financial reviews 
              ensure proper utilization of devotee contributions.
            </p>
          </div>
          
          <div class="trust-card">
            <h3>Advisory Council</h3>
            <p>
              While Thampuran holds final authority on ritual matters, an informal advisory council of 
              respected community elders provides guidance on administrative decisions, ensuring the temple 
              serves the broader community's spiritual needs.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Contact & Consultation -->
  <section class="consultation-section">
    <div class="thampuran-container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2>Personal Consultation with Thampuran</h2>
      </div>
      
      <div class="consultation-content">
        <div class="consultation-info">
          <h3>When to Seek Personal Guidance</h3>
          <p>While most poojas can be booked online or through the temple office, personal consultation 
          with Ambotti Thampuran is recommended for:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Severe or complex spiritual problems requiring detailed assessment</li>
            <li>Uncertainty about which pooja or remedy is most appropriate</li>
            <li>Major life decisions requiring spiritual guidance</li>
            <li>Planning elaborate ceremonies like Kala Sarpa Bali</li>
            <li>Guidance on post-pooja practices and follow-through</li>
            <li>Questions about ancestral karma or generational issues</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        
        <div class="consultation-booking">
          <h3>How to Arrange Consultation</h3>
          <div class="booking-steps">
            <div class="step">
              <span class="step-number">1</span>
              <div class="step-content">
                <h4>Call Temple Office</h4>
                <p>+91 9946373522 or +91 491 2552910</p>
                <p class="step-note">Available during temple hours: 5:30-10:30 AM, 5:30-7:30 PM</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="step">
              <span class="step-number">2</span>
              <div class="step-content">
                <h4>Schedule Appointment</h4>
                <p>Consultations typically available on specific days (inquire when calling)</p>
                <p class="step-note">In-person preferred, but phone consultation possible for distant devotees</p>
              </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="step">
              <span class="step-number">3</span>
              <div class="step-content">
                <h4>Prepare Information</h4>
                <p>Bring or be ready to share: Birth details (date, time, place), family background, 
                specific problems/concerns, any previous remedies attempted</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <div class="consultation-cta">
            <a href="tel:+919946373522" class="btn-consultation">Call to Schedule Consultation</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Quote -->
  <section class="quote-section">
    <div class="quote-container">
      <div class="quote-mark">"</div>
      <blockquote>
        Our duty is to preserve what the ancestors entrusted to us—not just the temple buildings or 
        rituals, but the living spiritual power that flows through these sacred grounds. When a devotee 
        comes seeking help, they are not just seeking a ceremony. They are seeking the grace of the 
        Divine Nagas, the blessings of Kashyapa Maharshi, and the accumulated power of countless 
        prayers offered here over centuries. This is what we protect, nurture, and pass forward.
      </blockquote>
      <cite>— Ambotti Thampuran, Temple Administrator</cite>
    </div>
  </section>

</Layout>

<style>
/* Thampuran Page Styles */
.thampuran-hero {
  position: relative;
  min-height: 60vh;
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  background: 
    linear-gradient(rgba(82, 14, 9, 0.85), rgba(82, 14, 9, 0.85)),
    url('/images/Ambotti.jpg') center/cover;
  padding: 8rem 2rem 4rem;
  text-align: center;
}

.thampuran-hero-overlay {
  position: absolute;
  top: 0;
  left: 0;
  right: 0;
  bottom: 0;
  background: radial-gradient(circle at 50% 50%, rgba(212, 165, 116, 0.15) 0%, transparent 70%);
}

.thampuran-hero-content {
  max-width: 800px;
  position: relative;
  z-index: 10;
}

.thampuran-hero h1 {
  font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
  font-size: 4.5rem;
  font-weight: 700;
  color: white;
  margin-bottom: 1rem;
  text-shadow: 2px 2px 4px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3);
}

.thampuran-hero p {
  font-size: 1.5rem;
  color: var(--gold-light);
  line-height: 1.6;
  font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
  font-weight: 600;
}

.thampuran-container {
  max-width: 1200px;
  margin: 0 auto;
  padding: 0 2rem;
}

.section-header {
  text-align: center;
  margin-bottom: 3rem;
}

.section-label {
  display: inline-block;
  font-size: 0.9rem;
  color: var(--gold);
  text-transform: uppercase;
  letter-spacing: 3px;
  margin-bottom: 1rem;
  font-weight: 600;
}

.section-header h2 {
  font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
  font-size: 3rem;
  font-weight: 700;
  color: var(--laterite-red);
  margin-bottom: 1rem;
}

/* Intro Section */
.intro-section {
  padding: 6rem 2rem;
  background: var(--bg-base);
}

.intro-content {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 400px 1fr;
  gap: 4rem;
  align-items: start;
}

.intro-image {
  position: sticky;
  top: 6rem;
}

.intro-image img {
  width: 100%;
  border-radius: 15px;
  box-shadow: 0 15px 50px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.15);
  border: 5px solid var(--gold);
}

.image-caption {
  text-align: center;
  margin-top: 1rem;
  font-size: 0.95rem;
  color: var(--text-muted);
  font-style: italic;
}

.intro-text h2 {
  font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
  font-size: 2.5rem;
  font-weight: 700;
  color: var(--laterite-red);
  margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
}

.intro-lead {
  font-size: 1.3rem;
  line-height: 1.8;
  color: var(--laterite-dark);
  font-weight: 500;
  margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
}

.intro-text p {
  font-size: 1.1rem;
  line-height: 1.9;
  color: var(--text-muted);
  margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
}

/* Lineage Section */
.lineage-section {
  padding: 6rem 2rem;
  background: var(--bg-alt);
}

.lineage-intro {
  font-size: 1.2rem;
  line-height: 1.9;
  color: var(--text-muted);
  max-width: 900px;
  margin: 0 auto 3rem;
  text-align: center;
}

.tradition-grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(320px, 1fr));
  gap: 2.5rem;
}

.tradition-card {
  background: var(--bg-base);
  padding: 2.5rem;
  border-radius: 15px;
  box-shadow: 0 8px 30px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.08);
  text-align: center;
}

.tradition-icon {
  font-size: 3.5rem;
  margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
}

.tradition-card h3 {
  font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
  font-size: 1.8rem;
  font-weight: 700;
  color: var(--laterite-red);
  margin-bottom: 1rem;
}

.tradition-card p {
  font-size: 1.05rem;
  line-height: 1.8;
  color: var(--text-muted);
}

/* Vision Section */
.vision-section {
  padding: 6rem 2rem;
  background: var(--bg-base);
}

.vision-grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr));
  gap: 2.5rem;
}

.vision-card {
  background: var(--bg-alt);
  padding: 2.5rem;
  border-radius: 15px;
  border-left: 5px solid var(--gold);
}

.vision-card.primary {
  background: var(--laterite-dark);
  border-left-color: var(--gold-light);
}

.vision-card h3 {
  font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
  font-size: 1.6rem;
  font-weight: 700;
  color: var(--laterite-red);
  margin-bottom: 1rem;
}

.vision-card.primary h3 {
  color: var(--gold-light);
}

.vision-card p {
  font-size: 1.05rem;
  line-height: 1.8;
  color: var(--text-muted);
}

.vision-card.primary p {
  color: var(--bg-alt);
  font-style: italic;
}

/* Responsibilities */
.responsibilities-section {
  padding: 6rem 2rem;
  background: var(--bg-alt);
}

.responsibilities-grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(280px, 1fr));
  gap: 2.5rem;
}

.duty-card {
  background: var(--bg-base);
  padding: 2rem;
  border-radius: 15px;
  box-shadow: 0 8px 30px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.08);
}

.duty-card h3 {
  font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
  font-size: 1.5rem;
  font-weight: 700;
  color: var(--laterite-red);
  margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  padding-bottom: 1rem;
  border-bottom: 3px solid var(--gold-light);
}

.duty-card ul {
  list-style: none;
  padding: 0;
}

.duty-card li {
  padding: 0.8rem 0;
  padding-left: 1.8rem;
  position: relative;
  border-bottom: 1px solid var(--bg-alt);
  line-height: 1.6;
}

.duty-card li:last-child {
  border-bottom: none;
}

.duty-card li::before {
  content: '•';
  position: absolute;
  left: 0;
  color: var(--gold);
  font-size: 1.5rem;
}

/* Preservation Section */
.preservation-section {
  padding: 6rem 2rem;
  background: var(--bg-base);
}

.preservation-intro {
  font-size: 1.3rem;
  line-height: 1.9;
  color: var(--laterite-dark);
  max-width: 900px;
  margin: 0 auto 3rem;
  text-align: center;
  font-style: italic;
  font-weight: 500;
}

.preservation-grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(320px, 1fr));
  gap: 2.5rem;
}

.preservation-item {
  background: var(--bg-alt);
  padding: 2.5rem;
  border-radius: 15px;
  border-top: 4px solid var(--laterite-red);
}

.preservation-item h3 {
  font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
  font-size: 1.8rem;
  font-weight: 700;
  color: var(--laterite-red);
  margin-bottom: 1rem;
}

.preservation-item p {
  font-size: 1.05rem;
  line-height: 1.8;
  color: var(--text-muted);
  margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
}

.btn-preservation {
  display: inline-block;
  padding: 1rem 2rem;
  background: var(--laterite-red);
  color: white;
  text-decoration: none;
  border-radius: 2px;
  font-weight: 600;
  transition: all 0.3s ease;
}

.btn-preservation:hover {
  background: var(--saffron);
  transform: translateY(-3px);
}

/* Trust Section */
.trust-section {
  padding: 6rem 2rem;
  background: var(--bg-alt);
}

.trust-intro {
  font-size: 1.2rem;
  line-height: 1.9;
  color: var(--text-muted);
  max-width: 900px;
  margin: 0 auto 3rem;
  text-align: center;
}

.trust-grid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(320px, 1fr));
  gap: 2.5rem;
}

.trust-card {
  background: var(--bg-base);
  padding: 2.5rem;
  border-radius: 15px;
  box-shadow: 0 8px 30px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.08);
}

.trust-card h3 {
  font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
  font-size: 1.6rem;
  font-weight: 700;
  color: var(--laterite-red);
  margin-bottom: 1rem;
}

.trust-card p {
  font-size: 1.05rem;
  line-height: 1.8;
  color: var(--text-muted);
}

/* Consultation Section */
.consultation-section {
  padding: 6rem 2rem;
  background: var(--bg-base);
}

.consultation-content {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
  gap: 4rem;
}

.consultation-info h3,
.consultation-booking h3 {
  font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
  font-size: 1.8rem;
  font-weight: 700;
  color: var(--laterite-red);
  margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
}

.consultation-info p {
  font-size: 1.1rem;
  line-height: 1.8;
  color: var(--text-muted);
  margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
}

.consultation-info ul {
  margin: 0 0 0 1.5rem;
}

.consultation-info li {
  margin-bottom: 0.8rem;
  line-height: 1.7;
}

.booking-steps {
  margin-bottom: 2rem;
}

.step {
  display: flex;
  gap: 1.5rem;
  margin-bottom: 2rem;
  padding: 1.5rem;
  background: var(--bg-alt);
  border-radius: 12px;
}

.step-number {
  width: 50px;
  height: 50px;
  background: var(--laterite-red);
  color: white;
  border-radius: 50%;
  display: flex;
  align-items: center;
  justify-content: center;
  font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
  font-size: 1.8rem;
  font-weight: 700;
  flex-shrink: 0;
}

.step-content h4 {
  font-family: 'Cormorant Garamond', serif;
  font-size: 1.3rem;
  font-weight: 700;
  color: var(--laterite-red);
  margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
}

.step-content p {
  font-size: 1.05rem;
  color: var(--text-muted);
  line-height: 1.7;
  margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
}

.step-note {
  font-size: 0.95rem;
  color: #666;
